caption: Mannnnn..... listen. Long story short. I just moved up here from SC. Love Chinese food. We have that down there. So you’d think it would be here in abundance. Searched far and wide to get some bomb a$& General Tso chicken from Bambao! Bow! It was the stop in the corner for me!

The bubble teas (alcoholic or non), especially the raven's rum (spiked taro) are great. The food is so bad that I'm genuinely baffled by all of the good reviews here. To each their own but there was legitimately nothing redeemable about it. Oversalted, overcooked (the vegetables are basically mush) and over... vinegar-ed. This plus the fact that they obviously give you way too much rice so they can skimp on the vegetables/ protein. Also worth mentioning it's literally exactly the same as the food from Manchurian Rice Co.
When I had went to bambaos I ordered apple tea Boba and shrimp lo main The shrimp lo main was so nasty I couldn't even finish it  I would only go to bambaos for Boba thats it
Bamboo was quiet, food was good, very clean
Best bubble tea!
Beautiful atmosphere. Clean. Fast prep. Highly recommend SAMBAL FRIED CHICKEN.

Good portions great food. Definitely try the coconut pudding. We've eaten here again and again and the quality is always excellent. The staff is so friendly and fast!! Highly recommend, just excellent.
Love there bubble tea

Been here a few times now and can honestly say it depends on when you go and who's working for what experience you'll get. The first time I was there the customer service was bad, the milk tea had no taste and too much ice, the food was ok but more veggithan meat and even when I asked to have it fixed they just remade it the same way. Second time was way better. They actually listened to my notes so everything came out how I liked it. Their Taro Milk Tea is amazing. I love the mongolian beef. Best advice is be specific about what you want and like!
Great ambiance and superb customer service. The food tastes amazing also. Highly recommended.
taro milk tea with almond milk is fabulous!
Great food
Good was great! We had never heard of this place but decided to give it a try.  The Bulgogi Beef was excellent!  Try it, you'll thank me later.
General tso’s chicken was probably the best I’ve ever had
Good quality food. I ordered general Tso chicken. Decent portion and wasn’t super greasy. Loved it
Really good food always, but whenever I just try to call in I have to call at least 3 times each time I want some food. Just had to call 20 times and its only 7
It was a first for us. Something different. It was nice.

This site is my favorite restaurant.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to this restaurant. when  I I need a special supper, this place comes right away to my head. excellent and diverse  food and a large menu.courteous crew, and pleasant atmosphere. Also important, the cost is honest. I praise this place with great pleasure.
It was amazing. The Mongolian beef was great. Unfortunately, we didn't really understand how to eat the Bao.
I get lunch here often and they never disappoint. Good food, good portions, quick service.

Love the food here and they have the best boba I’ve ever had but I saw a girl eating behind the counter in front of orders being made and it was kinda gross especially during the pandemic but I had already ordered my food.
The mongolian beef is awesome!
Delicious Bubble Tea
The baos are incredible and the Chinese food is the best and highest quality I’ve found in the city. My new favorite restaurant in Baltimore!
Amazing food! Cauli rice option delish with any of the bowls 👍

This place as quickly become my families go to restaurant for asian cuisine.Although, personally we don't like any of their Baos, their classic menus is unreal and so so so good, particularly Mongolian beef and fried rice, very basic dishes but they do it so so right. 5/5 Love love love.

Ordered to go due to the lockdown. Didn't receive my Bubble Tea, which is the reason I ordered from this establishment in the first place. Crab Rangoons were amazing, Dumplings were average, and the Popcorn Chicken was awful.
Food looked delicious and it was! Great taste and very fresh. We wanted something different to eat and now we love it. Well worth the price. We will be back!

Well, we live right across the street so we ate there a few times. When ordering on app it takes 20-25 minutes. My problem with the food is the inconsistencies! Today we ordered the rice with fried chicken, some chunks were fried some grilled, last time it was fried but a much smaller dish. my vegetarian wife got the bao with some inedible chunks of burned mushrooms that hurt her teeth, and fried rice with real burned egg in it. The salted caramel drink was nice, though it seems to be with milk on the web. Anyway, lately they're disappointing and that's quite a shame since we do love asian food and they're really close.

We Loved the Chinese meals.  Very good quality, prices, and fun.  A very safe location and walking option for me and students For often visits.  Quote and painting in inside is not from China?  Logo is correct it means pure in Chinese. 💝
Surprised it wasn’t packed on a beautiful day. Food & service was great. Only complaints have to do with decor. It’s uncomfortably ugly, dark, and pulled from dated magazine clippings.

Went for lunch today (Friday). Only one person waiting for their takeaway so no wait to place order.  We ordered popcorn chicken, lemongrass grilled chicken on a bao, and sambal honey fried chicken bowl. The order was cooked fresh and was ready in  roughly 5-10 minutes. Popcorn chicken was great, recommend slightly less seasoning then these are a home run. The lemongrass grilled chicken bao was cooked perfectly and great taste. Only issue is the bao was soggy in places. My wife enjoyed her Sambal Chicken bowl. The pickled cabbage is awesome! Seating is upstairs via a twisted staircase (leave your stroller in the car) and there is seating for probably 20.

Excellent bao. I got the Lemongrass Grilled Chicken Bao and a Taro Milk Tea.  The chicken was excellent and had the right balance of lemongrass and the side of napa cabbage salad was excellent! The taro milk tea was also high quality. I didn’t try the boba tho. It is a elegant looking location with a 2nd floor dining area.
Some vegetarian options, slow
Great little spot for Habor East space.I love the focus on sustainability and the use of the space. I got the beef bulgolgi bowl with white rice and it was really good.
A solid contender for best bubble tea in Baltimore. The teriyaki pork rib bowl with pearl barley was 10/10. I dream about that bowl even though I am trying to cut down on my red meat consumption
Great buns and dumplings
Food was excellent, one of the owners was onsite on-site and gave me a coupon, so extra nice. Not many places do bao this well.
Not only is the food absolutely AMAZING, the staff and atmosphere is a 10/10! This is a must-see Baltimore food destination! The beef bao and the dumplings are my favorite

I usually don’t write reviews but I came here yesterday, and I tried the bubble tea - Thai Tea and I have to say it was really good! The food was delicious as well. The only downside was where you order the food- it was freezing cold. When I asked if that was normal they said yes. I don’t think people should be working in those conditions or customers should be uncomfortable while they order their meal. Also, when I got there it was a bit busy, and there were two employees in the back and two in the front, and my meal still came out quick and HOT!
The best bubble ever and food was great su day

Been in there twice now - once on the unofficial opening day and once today. Both times the wait was nearly unbearable. The first visit was nearly 30 minutes to receive a simple bao bun. Food itself was nothing special and was certainly overpriced which soured the experience that much more. Today it took 20 minutes to receive a few bubble teas. The tea itself was good but not worth my 20 minutes of waiting. While waiting for my tea, a man was talking to employees about being served raw meat in potstickers. I managed to catch a glance myself and they were indeed raw. I will take my business to better establishments that actually have quality product - Ekiben and Simply Sip Tea. This place is just banking on the popularity explosion of LA-styled asian food and boba without being the real deal. Avoid.
The tofu bowl was amazing and the trumpet mushrooms were possibly the best I’ve ever had!! This is a great addition to harbor east.
We got a lot of stuff to sample and share- loved the fried chicken bao, dumplings, crab rangoon, and popcorn chicken! We also tried the Thai tea and taro tea with boba- both great!

Overall a great first experience! I ordered the beef bulgogi bun and it was absolutely delicious. The bubble tea was even better! The food was also made very quickly and the design is beautiful. Would definitely recommend!!!
This place had very high expectations and unfortunately it has come short. Food was ok, nothing exciting about it, especially for what you’re paying.
Decent food but overpriced.
I had the beef short rib bowl. The beef was just ok and the rice was mushy and overcooked.  Not worth the nearly $15
The staff was super friendly and the teriyaki pork felt like it melted in my mouth. I also enjoyed the touch of fried ginger in my bowl and the cauliflower rice was well made

One chicken boa to go please! I enjoyed my visit to this new spot near my job. As I walked in I was greeted with a smile and ask if I needed any help since this was my first time. I took a menu and looked for something tasty and I found it. I ordered sambal honey fried chicken and a side of crab rangoon to go. Food arrived in about 5-8 minutes and hot and ready to eat. Music was low and nice for a quiet 2pm day. I miss the lunch crowd, happy to say. The decor was beautiful and well put together. I would suggest to stop by and try it out. I would say it does add up in price. I spent $17, more then normal for my lunch budget. But it was still good and had a nice fully meal. Check it out if your in the inner harbor .

This place is awesome. I decided to venture out and try something different. Newly opened with excellent service. Greeted and checked on thru out my meal while it was super busy. Daniel C. made sure everything was handled and guests were happy. I had a great Friday dinner. Check it out! 🙂

It is so worth driving down town just to have the most delicious vegetable fried rice Bambao style. Beautiful blend of delicious and fresh ingredients that evoke comforting and memorable experience. Peaceful atmosphere and very pleasant staff are bonus! So worth it!!
I love their fried chicken bao and original milk tea + cheese foam 😍 also not sure what they put into their dumpling dipping sauce but it’s out of this world 👌

Love it! The buns and bowls are delicious and affordable. Chef Cyrus Keefer is a magician at his craft opening another great restaurant in Baltimore. You're doing yourself an injustice if you are not there right now.

I struggle between 2 - 3 stars for this. Lunch today was challenging. Our first outing here on their 2nd day open so I'll say they have room to improve. Taro boba tea was not bad but too much ice left it difficult to get the boba out and made my drink watered down in 10min. The ordering went quick and the food was ready fairly quickly. We sat upstairs at a comfortable round table with homey cushions and atmosphere. Our food was given in togo containers w/ lids and bags despite asking to eat in. I sampled a lot today: The pork & shrimp dumplings were amazing. This was the best thing on the menu by far. The popcorn chicken was a large portion with hearty dark meat but the breading was soggy. Maybe it shouldn't have been covered? Dipping sauce was spicy and excellent. The beef bulgogi was on the chewy side. The one piece I had wasn't bad, but my friend got tired of chewing thru the meal by the end. The teriyaki pork rib on bun was greasy and heavy with braised flavor. The portion size was good. The bun was a horrible mess and I couldn't finish it. It was rubbery like they microwaved the thing. It's offensive to call this wrap a bun because it was like a cheap pita wrapped around the meat. The buns need a total re-write. This one went to the trash. The veggie fried rice was an abomination. They actually put imitation cream meat in a vegetarian dish and don't call it out on the menu. The dish tasted heavily of sesame oil so much so, that it became tiresome to eat. This one went to the trash. The Sambal honey fried chicken was ok. It is reminiscent of another local area shop's signature dish so comparisons come to mind when eating it and it fell short. The lemongrass chicken was reportedly the best dish, though was not breathtaking. It was just better than the rest. Overall this was a lot of disappointed people out for lunch. The price was high to spend for lunch, especially when it didn't satisfy. I'll admit we walked in with high expectations after watching the IG photos for weeks, but this place needs some more work to be worthy of stopping by. About $10 for lunch is a common standard and I blew past that to $24 w/o tip. It's unsustainable at that price point for what amounts to a simple lunch

The vegetable fried rice with chicken was absolutely phenomenal! I can't wait to try other items on the menu. The apple bubble tea was great as well. I can already tell it's going to become one of my go-to spots in the area.

An absolutely perfect spot for take-out or dine-in when craving Asian fusion without unreasonable prices. Boba tea, bowl options and bao, delicious plant based options and Asian twists on local favorites in the heart of Harbor East. Great menu, clean space, awesome staff, eco-friendly packaging, and responsible management. Love that they invited the community to be a part of the restaurant. If you're on the fence, jump. It's well worth it.

Buns taste better than Ekiben’s which was a surprise!! Great addition to Harbor East. Went for lunch hoping the food would live up to the hype on Insta and it did not disappoint! Try the Asian fried chicken bun. Very good! Stephanie Bradshaw did the interior design according to their account. Fail. Just ugly. Uncomfortable seats, office stools instead of chairs, random mural of paper birds, sloppy paint, bad lighting, futon by the door. Really? Get rid of that thing! lol Come for the food, clean bathrooms, friendly staff, and great location. Will return. Would recommend.
Today I tried Bambao for the 1st time, I did the fried chicken it was awesome - great new lunch venue in the Inner Harbour!!

I wanted this to be Ekiben, but in a more convenient location. It is not. The Sambal fried chicken was soggy, with chewy bits and possibly not cooked through. I know they are trying and I know it's new, but the flavors were not there. For the price, I'd rather take the walk to Ekiben - larger portions and amazing flavors. Bubble tea was okay. Lots of ice and the bubbles had an unexpected burnt marshmallow taste. I prefer the walk to iFusion for that.
I am here on the very first day of being open for business. Management and kind and attentive. Diverse, polite and professional staff. WONDERFUL bubble tea and food!
Great location and the chicken in the Bao was perfect!   This will definitely become a regular in our lunch rotation!
